{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "04", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "05", "M": "23", "S": "05"}}, "news": [{"title": "To generate revenue, Ludhiana civic body eyes sale of commercial properties", "para": "Facing financial strain, Ludhiana's civic body is set to auction its commercial properties, aiming to raise \u20b950 crore in the fiscal year 2026-27.  Sixty-five shop-cum-offices in Shaheed Bhagat Singh Nagar and other prime locations are slated for sale. Officials are benchmarking rates against other development authorities to maximize revenue from these valuable assets.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/ludhiana-civic-body-plans-revenue-boost-through-commercial-property-sales/130744790?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-73196/130744790.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Indiramma housing phase-II soon, bid to fix issues: Telangana minister", "para": "Telangana's Revenue and Housing Minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy announced the imminent launch of the second phase of the Indiramma housing scheme. He highlighted the government's efforts to resolve land record issues and criticized the previous BRS government for failing to fulfill its housing promises. Reddy also reiterated the Congress government's commitment to farmers' welfare, citing crop procurement and loan waivers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/telanganas-indiramma-housing-phase-ii-launches-amid-opposition-criticism/130744623?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-54028/130744623.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "BMC initiates integration of 3D digital model of Mumbai with civic systems", "para": "The BMC is integrating its 3D digital model of Mumbai with key civic systems to enhance transparency and efficiency. This digital twin will aid in precise assessment of development charges and property tax, detect unauthorized constructions, and streamline approval processes. The system will also support infrastructure planning and disaster management by providing detailed urban landscape data.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/bmc-initiates-integration-of-3d-digital-model-of-mumbai-with-civic-systems/130744480?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-59604/130744480.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}]}